stylometry: Some of the variables you must consider would be holding costs, lead times, re-order points and your estimated order quantities.  In the restaurant business this method is used quite frequently.  As a manager of a store you must look at your weelky sales of each piece of inventory you did or did not sell.  If you have too much of a certain product and it does not sell the shelf life will depreciate and therefore you will be losing money.  The same can be said if you do not have enough inventory your guests will not be happy and you will also lose money.  When looking over weekly sales it is important to order the right amount so that you are not holding too much of one or more items. This is why safety stock is so important becasue if you have a busy weekend, you want order of something to cover yourself.  Another good way I like to think of safety stock is like buying care insurance.  Do you buy full coverage or just pay for liabilities.
